playbackDescription.title: Brute Force Tic-Tac-Toe
playbackDescription.description:
This program builds on a previous program to build a tree of every possible game that can be played of tic-tac-toe. There are 255,168 distinct games that can be played on a 3X3 board and this program plays every single one of them. It counts how many games player X wins (X always goes first), O wins, and the number of draws.

In order to play this many games the program needs a way to systematically create game boards and advance them one move at a time. I use a custom tree data type to hold all of the games. After I create all of the games and count them I clean up the memory I allocate along the way.

I will not use any particular strategy or intelligence in this program. I will create every move possible no matter how dumb it may seem. My goal is to store every possible game in the tree.
